    "Reason : 1 - The proposed extension by virtue of it's signifcant size, scale and depth is considered to be dominant and discordant within the terrace and would have an adverses visuaal impact on the character and appearance of the host property, the wider terrace and the East Canonbury Conservation Area. The application therefore fails to accord with the NPPF (2019), policies 7.4, 7.6 and 7.8 of London Plan (2016), policies CS8 and CS9 of the Islington Core Strategy (2011), policies DM2.1 and DM2.3 of the Islington Development Management Policies (2013), and the guidance contained within the Urban Design Guide (2017) and the Conservation Area Design Guidelines (2002).\r\n",
